item.title: Safari 4 has converted me.
item.dc:creator: OldDirtyBastard
item.description:
If you have slow internet, it blows at loading images, because it loads them as it views them on the page, and not beforehand. Even if it’s done everything in the current frame, it doesn’t continue to go down and load more images, just stops where it’s at.

There are also certain differences between the way in which different browsers load content.
